int max = nums[n - 1];
ans.add(max);

for (int i = n - 2; i >= 0; i--) {
    if (nums[i] > max) {
        ans.add(nums[i]);
        max = nums[i];
    }
}

Time Complexity: O(N), where N is the size of the input array. This is because we traverse the array only once.

Space Complexity: O(1), as we are using only a constant amount of extra space.
